      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/05/29/lack-of-response-to-critical-vulnerability-in-gogs-is-a-reminder-of-the-limits-of-open-source-projects.webp" alt="Lack of response to critical vulnerability in Gogs is a reminder of the limits of open source projects" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Lack of response to critical vulnerability in Gogs is a reminder of the limits of open source projects</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      A newly discovered and so far unpatched critical vulnerability in the open source Gogs Git service not only demands immediate action from developers to secure their code, it also puts a spotlight on the potential issues in using self-hosted code platforms from small maintainers.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/05/29/lack-of-response-to-critical-vulnerability-in-gogs-is-a-reminder-of-the-limits-of-open-source-projects/"  >(Info World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</div><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Mon, 25 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Mon, 25 May 2026 09:00:00 GMT">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Info World">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static14/tech/2026/05/25/the-role-of-mcp-in-context-engineering.webp" alt="The role of MCP in context engineering" itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
        onerror="this.parentNode.style.display='none'" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">The role of MCP in context engineering</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      There’s no denying the excitement around Model Context Protocol (MCP), an open protocol for connecting AI assistants with external data, tools, and APIs. Since its debut by Anthropic in late 2024, thousands of MCP servers have emerged for devops, cloud, and beyond.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2026/05/25/the-role-of-mcp-in-context-engineering/"  >(Info World)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
